Responsibilities:

Responsibilities the online marketing activities and website contents to capture profitable growth;
Formulate and implement customized annual promotion plan, ensure to meet the business target and maximize the brand image exposure within the budget;
Plan and develop the loyalty program, marketing campaigns, CRM initiatives to optimize profitability;
Monitor business results and campaigns effectiveness;
Keep track the market trend and competitors promotional and marketing programs/ activities;       
Perform ad hoc assignments.

Requirements:


Bachelor Degree in Marketing or related disciplines;
Minimum 3 years experience in Beauty centre / reatil is an advantage;
A good team player with strong communication and interpersonal skills;
Attention in details with analytical and presentation skills;
Energetic, proactive, creative with a good sense in beauty;
Good command in spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Marketing Executive;
Immediately available is highly preferred 

Working Location: Lai Chi Kok

We offer 5-day work and a competitive salary and benefits package for the right candidate. To apply online please click the 'Apply' button below with your resume, current & expected salary, and availability to us.

Personal data collected will be treated in strict confidence and be used for recruitment purposes only.

Job Description

Locate new business opportunities as potential digital marketing products both independently and under the guidance of team leader;
Prospecting, identifying and acquiring new HK based clients for selling online marketing advertising solutions (e.g. WeChat/China Advertising/China KOLs,etc);
Follow up sales Leads, prepare sales pitch and agreements with marketing team;
Maintain good relationships with clients, regular review and up-selling various advertising solutions to enhance their advertising performance/effect;
Execute inhouse media investment plan by working closely with Marketing Director to enhance the market impact of Our Company;
Manage clients’ projects, including defining deliverables, schedule and setting milestones, resources planning, coordinating internal resources, expectation management, launch, KPI tracking and post-campaign evaluation, etc.

The Successful Applicant

1-4 years Sales or Marketing / Advertising / PR experience;
Online-media savvy is a big advantage;
Knowledge in China media (social media, KOLs, Tencent, Douyin, Xiaohongshu, Video platform, etc), but not a must, training will be delivered;
Creative, Dynamic, embracing changes personally;
Good communication skills in both English & Chinese;
Immediate availability is preferred;
Candidate with higher qualification and relevant working experience will be considered as Senior Business Development Executive / Assistant Business Development Manager.

What's On Offer

Attractive Remuneration Package and Benefits
Incentive & commission schemes will be offered
5-day work
Bank Holidays and other special leave (e.g. Birthday Leave, Wedding Leave and Family Leave, etc.)
Medical Insurance
Sales and Product training will be provided
Team Building Activities
Opportunity for Job Promotion
Friendly Work Environment
Interest parties please send your CV with availability, current and expected salary to us.

**Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only**

