This is an exciting opportunity for an outstanding candidate who is passionate and responsible to develop and implement CRM solutions to engage, retain, upsell & recruit customers, and leverage insight and data.




VIP & CRM Program management 


Plan and deliver CRM strategies across the brand for both online and offline encouraging customer retention, improving customer loyalty and promoting the brand;
Design loyalty program, customer journey automation & CRM activities to engage customers, build sustainable growth on membership lifetime value;
Turn data of customer analytic & customer journey mapping into actionable customer insights maximize commercial opportunities;
Work closely with sales and planning  departments to ensure the CRM works effectively and ensure smooth execution of in-store promotion;
Ensuring CRM communications and database segmentation effectiveness for targeted marketing activities in respect to local & overseas customers’ purchase behaviours;
Manage and monitor data acquisition strategy.

Strategic partnership

Develop and execute partnership acquisition strategies with potential partners in bank, retail, hotel, and other sectors;
To strengthen the loyalty program's variety, maximize the program's popularity, and assist the Sales team to achieve revenue target of the overall business;
Manage program's communications content including social media, website, eDM & SMS;
Managing overall inventory level to ensure the effective operation of the loyalty program;
Conduct regular reports for internal review.

Shopping Mall Promotion

Work with shopping malls to support business needs with various collaboration;
Liaise with internal parties and landlords for organizing marketing and promotion events at the shopping mall to enhance quality traffic and business revenue.

Requirements and Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree required, preferably in Marketing, Communication, Public Relations,  Business Statistics, Information System Management or related discipline;
Proven track record of managing CRM data systems, implementing CRM program and campaign management;
4+ years relevant work experience in a fashion/beauty retail environment;
Good knowledge in data-driven and CRM-focused mindset is a must;
Highly organized and detail-minded.  Comfortable working under tight deadlines and managing multiple projects simultaneously;
Obsessed with customers and experience with campaign measurements (effectiveness/ efficiency);
Strong analytical mind with good report writing skills, and able to transform data into actionable insight;
Excellent written and verbal English and Chinese communication skills is a must;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as "Marketing Executive".
We offer excellent career prospects, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.  Please apply in strict confidence by sending personal resume together with salary expected and date available

by email to: h r d _ h n @ h a r v e y n i c h o l s . c o m . h k
We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not notified within eight weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months. A copy of our Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request by contacting our Human Resources Division.

Your role:

Responsible for lead generation and prepare tracking reports to support various marketing campaigns;
Develop Dashboards to facilitate efficient data analysis for product performance, customer profiles and campaign effectiveness;
Conduct quantitative analysis and data mining to support management decisions and provide data-driven recommendations;
Organize and prepare regular reports relating to business performance and service usage;
Conduct user acceptance test of in-house-developed applications.

To succeed in this role

University graduate in Computer Science, Information Technology, Data Science, Statistics or relevant discipline;
3 – 4 years’ relevant experience, preferably in data analysis, database programming or database management
Proficient in SAS, SQL, Python or other data mining tools;
Practical experience in data visualization tools (e.g. Qlik View/Sense, Power BI or Tableau);
Good analytical and problem solving skills, able to work under tight timeline;
Self-motivated and able to accomplish multiple tasks with minimal supervision;
Good interpersonal and communication skills and able to work with people at all levels;
Good command in both spoken and written English;
Candidate with less experience will be considered for the position of Senior Customer Data Analyst.

HKT is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and will only be used for recruitment-related purposes. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with the employer's privacy statement (http://www.hkt.com/privacy-statement), a copy of which will be provided immediately upon request.

Work on the portfolio with the RMs and identify business opportunities to achieve competitive edge for deposits and employee banking services. Assist to formulate and implement personal customer segment strategies to achieve the business targets and improve customer experience. Design and monitor the implementation of segment business plans through initiatives/ activities on acquisition, cross-selling, service upgrade, customer loyalty and retention, etc. Work with various internal and external stakeholders to meet customers’ needs from a holistic perspective. Design appropriate sales tools to facilitate frontline to achieve the planned business targets and objectives. Collect and analyze data and feedbacks from time to time and make business recommendations for continuous improvement.

Requirements:

Degree or above with major in Business Administration, Marketing, Finance or related discipline;
At least 5 years working experience in banking industry; experience in customer segmentation, marketing, or product management is preferred;
With sales experience in retail banking and familiar with banking products and operations/services enhancement will be an advantage;
A good team player with strong business acumen and analytical skills;
Excellent communication and presentation skills;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua is preferable.

If you are flexible enough and zeal for a harmonious and supportive working environment where enables you to grow and succeed professionally, please send a full resume indicating your public examination results (HKCEE and HKALE / HKDSE), your present and expected salary and quoting reference number attention to Talent Acquisition Division, Nanyang Commercial Bank, 151 Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong or apply through email. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hk/ and select the page Recruit.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 12 months of receipt.
